{
  "text": "In this paper, we focus on the flooding-based attack aiming at layer 3/layer 4 in the OSI 7-layer model and apply the decision tree (C4.5) technique to detect abnormal traffic flow [CITATION_1] . Then we use a novel traffic pattern matching procedure to identify the traffic flow that is similar to the attack flow and, based on this similarity, to trace back the origin of an attack. The attack path reconstruction is accomplished by the protection agent and the sentinels.",
